---
Mafdet's Shrine of the First Claw maintains the Plague Mandate in its oath-violation case files with an unusual classification: the Mandate itself was not an oath violation, but its continued application after the emergency ended was.
Officers who continued applying cremation orders to non-plague dead and using intake authority for political detention had not technically violated the Mandate — they had violated the conditions under which the Mandate's authority was legitimate.
The Shrine's classification: continued application of Mandate powers after the crisis ended constitutes sustained oath violation by the officers applying it, distinct from the legitimate Mandate itself.
The Claw Mark Registry notes: three ships' captains from the Mandate period appear in the Registry with oath-violation notations for invoking Mandate authority at Mafdet harbor after the crisis period. All three were banned from Mafdet's trade network. Their bans remain active.

